rass.&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;dl&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Taken&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;2019-07-20&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Location&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;Canada / BC / Richmond / West Dyke Trail&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title>Photo of the day</title><link>https://rosschurchley.com/2025/animals-winter-horses/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://rosschurchley.com/2025/animals-winter-horses/</guid><pubDate>Fri, 18 Apr 2025 07:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/src.CFdzve8c_Z2rk1hB.webp&quot; width=6000 height=4000 alt=Two horses stand together in a field. One is brown, and the other has a spotted coat. The ground is covered in frost, and a forest of bare beech trees is in the background.&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;dl&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Taken&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;2019-12-01&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Location&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;Canada / BC / Kamloops&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title>Photo of the day</title><link>https://rosschurchley.com/2025/animals-turtle-gathering/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://rosschurchley.com/2025/animals-turtle-gathering/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 17 Apr 2025 07:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/src.CG1Gj1-M_1UtAug.webp&quot; width=6000 height=4000 alt=Three turtles sit on a dark log surrounded by green lily pads and white flowers in a pond.&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;dl&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Taken&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;2024-06-23&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Location&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;Canada / BC / Vancouver / VanDusen Botanical Garden&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title>Photo of the day</title><link>https://rosschurchley.com/2025/animals-ueno-fish/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://rosschurchley.com/2025/animals-ueno-fish/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 16 Apr 2025 07:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/src.C94EMgOq_EEwhl.webp&quot; width=6000 height=4000 alt=Two fish face the viewer, open mouths poking above the surface.&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;dl&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Taken&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;2024-11-21&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Location&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;Japan / Tōkyō / Taitō / Ueno Park&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title>Photo of the day</title><link>https://rosschurchley.com/2025/animals-pig/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://rosschurchley.com/2025/animals-pig/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 15 Apr 2025 07:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/src.BPPt3eU4_Z20x7mU.webp&quot; width=6000 height=4000 alt=A light grey pig stands in a grassy field, looking directly at the camera with a curious expression.&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;dl&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Taken&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;2019-09-07&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Location&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;Canada / BC / Kamloops&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title>Watercolour linocut</title><link>https://rosschurchley.com/2025/watercolour-linocut/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://rosschurchley.com/2025/watercolour-linocut/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 14 Apr 2025 07:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/src.DNPSxAGH_Z1XmAnl.webp&quot; width=2956 height=2217 alt=A seagull in blue ink stamped on top of a watercolour wash suggestive of a cloudy sky&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;p&gt;A couple weeks ago I did a beginner’s &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linocut&quot;&gt;linocut&lt;/a&gt; workshop at the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.slicevancouver.ca&quot;&gt;Slice of Life Art Gallery&lt;/a&gt; in East Vancouver. The process was fun and simple: sketch something on tracing paper, transfer the graphite onto a rubber block, then carve out the relief. We stamped our designs on watercolour backgrounds we painted at the start of the workshop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;astro-gallery class=&quot;astro-7bcnqnrw&quot;&gt; &lt;figure class=&quot;gallery astro-7bcnqnrw&quot;&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;images astro-7bcnqnrw&quot;&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;astro-7bcnqnrw&quot;&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/_astro/IMG_2319.YiI-bB83_1mxsYX.webp&quot; data-pswp-width=&quot;2772&quot; data-pswp-height=&quot;2079&quot; class=&quot;astro-7bcnqnrw&quot;&gt; &lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/IMG_2319.YiI-bB83_1mxsYX.webp&quot; srcset=&quot;/_astro/IMG_2319.YiI-bB83_ZtPneI.webp 640w, /_astro/IMG_2319.YiI-bB83_1CH1k4.webp 1024w, /_astro/IMG_2319.YiI-bB83_TTu4R.webp 1600w, /_astro/IMG_2319.YiI-bB83_1mxsYX.webp 2772w&quot; alt=&quot;A pencil sketch of a seagull silhouette on a pink rubber block.&quot; width=&quot;2772&quot; height=&quot;2079&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; class=&quot;astro-7bcnqnrw&quot;&gt; &lt;/a&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;astro-7bcnqnrw&quot;&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/_astro/IMG_2328.B7_-JGOj_Z2dvSu9.webp&quot; data-pswp-width=&quot;4032&quot; data-pswp-height=&quot;3024&quot; class=&quot;astro-7bcnqnrw&quot;&gt; &lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/IMG_2328.B7_-JGOj_Z2dvSu9.webp&quot; srcset=&quot;/_astro/IMG_2328.B7_-JGOj_ZzbpKg.webp 640w, /_astro/IMG_2328.B7_-JGOj_Z14YfGH.webp 1024w, /_astro/IMG_2328.B7_-JGOj_Z1MLLVT.webp 1600w, /_astro/IMG_2328.B7_-JGOj_Z2dvSu9.webp 4032w&quot; alt=&quot;A relief carving of a seagull made from a rubber block. The carving has been used as a stamp and has blue ink on it. A pile of pink shavings is in the background.&quot; width=&quot;4032&quot; height=&quot;3024&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; class=&quot;astro-7bcnqnrw&quot;&gt; &lt;/a&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;figcaption class=&quot;astro-7bcnqnrw&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The seagull stamp in progress.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt; &lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/astro-gallery&gt;  &lt;script type=&quot;module&quot; src=&quot;/home/runner/work/rosschurchley.com/rosschurchley.com/src/features/Gallery/Gallery.astro?astro&amp;type=script&amp;index=0&amp;lang.ts&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I made two designs — a simple seagull on a sky-blue background, and a more experimental depiction of a fire hydrant.&lt;sup id=&quot;fnref:1&quot; class=&quot;astro-ogpmuyat&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;fn-ref astro-ogpmuyat&quot; href=&quot;#fn:1&quot;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;   I’m quite pleased with how both turned out!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;astro-figure&gt; &lt;figure&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/_astro/IMG_2399.BHAq7lGQ_Z22CBFr.webp&quot; data-pswp-width=&quot;2374&quot; data-pswp-height=&quot;3324&quot;&gt; &lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/IMG_2399.BHAq7lGQ_Z22CBFr.webp&quot; srcset=&quot;/_astro/IMG_2399.BHAq7lGQ_2eDk3S.webp 640w, /_astro/IMG_2399.BHAq7lGQ_KbMKP.webp 1024w, /_astro/IMG_2399.BHAq7lGQ_Z1QrhKf.webp 1600w, /_astro/IMG_2399.BHAq7lGQ_Z22CBFr.webp 2374w&quot; alt=&quot;A black outline of a fire hydrant stamped on a watercolour background that evokes a red and yellow fire hydrant, a blue sky, and green grass.&quot; width=&quot;2374&quot; height=&quot;3324&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot;&gt; &lt;/a&gt; &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt; &lt;/figure&gt; &lt;/astro-figure&gt; &lt;script type=&quot;module&quot; src=&quot;/home/runner/work/rosschurchley.com/rosschurchley.com/src/features/Figure/Figure.astro?astro&amp;type=script&amp;index=0&amp;lang.ts&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;section class=&quot;footnotes astro-h4fc3wuz&quot;&gt; &lt;ol class=&quot;astro-h4fc3wuz&quot;&gt; &lt;li class=&quot;footnote&quot; id=&quot;fn:1&quot;&gt; &lt;p&gt;Eagle-eyed readers will notice that, although the watercolour gives the vibe of a fire hydrant, the &lt;a href=&quot;https://rosschurchley.com/2024/what-colour-is-a-fire-hydrant/&quot;&gt;colour scheme&lt;/a&gt; doesn’t exactly match that of anywhere in BC — all municipalities that have yellow-bodied hydrants with potentially red bonnets would also colour the side caps red. But that wouldn’t have come across in the medium.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ol&gt; &lt;/section&gt;  &lt;script type=&quot;module&quot; src=&quot;/home/runner/work/rosschurchley.com/rosschurchley.com/src/features/Footnote/FootnoteSection.astro?astro&amp;type=script&amp;index=0&amp;lang.ts&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title>Photo of the day</title><link>https://rosschurchley.com/2025/animals-crab/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://rosschurchley.com/2025/animals-crab/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 14 Apr 2025 07:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/src.DWMhN94m_ZuvTB6.webp&quot; width=6000 height=4000 alt=A dark crab stands on a wet sandy surface, partially submerged in the foam of an incoming wave.&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;dl&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Taken&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;2022-05-19&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Location&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;Canada / BC / Tofino&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title>Photo of the day</title><link>https://rosschurchley.com/2025/animals-squirrel/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://rosschurchley.com/2025/animals-squirrel/</guid><pubDate>Sun, 13 Apr 2025 07:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/src.C56683LS_t34Gx.webp&quot; width=6000 height=4000 alt=A squirrel sits on a log, holding and eating a seed with its paws.&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;dl&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Taken&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;2019-06-23&lt;/dd&gt;&