c=&quot;/_astro/src.BsqdAel3_1UpxkL.webp&quot; width=3846 height=2574 alt=An empty red cargo ship is moored at sea. The clear sky has the pastel colours of sunset, transitioning from red at the horizon to greenish-blue at the top of the frame. The cranes on the cargo ship are reflected on the calm waters.&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;dl&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Taken&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;2018-03-10&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Location&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;Canada / BC / Salish Sea&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title>Photo of the day</title><link>https://rosschurchley.com/2025/boats-steveston-pacific-viking/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://rosschurchley.com/2025/boats-steveston-pacific-viking/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 05 Mar 2025 08:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/src.D6utPb6X_LETCg.webp&quot; width=5754 height=3836 alt=A fishing boat covered with spherical orange buoys passes through the entrance to a cove marked by a beacon on a breakwater.&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;dl&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Taken&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;2022-05-21&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Location&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;Canada / BC / Richmond / Steveston&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title>Photo of the day</title><link>https://rosschurchley.com/2025/boats-ferry-lens-flare/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://rosschurchley.com/2025/boats-ferry-lens-flare/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 04 Mar 2025 08:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/src.DUyGLkVR_ZR7SRE.webp&quot; width=2304 height=3072 alt=A black-and-white photo showing the silhouette of a ferry in the glare of the sun on the water.&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;dl&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Taken&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;2009-07-19&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Location&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;Canada / BC / Salish Sea&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title>Unicode calligraphy: glottal stop</title><link>https://rosschurchley.com/2025/unicode-calligraphy-glottal-stop/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://rosschurchley.com/2025/unicode-calligraphy-glottal-stop/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 03 Mar 2025 08:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/src.B3lo571t_v4xc0.webp&quot; width=2328 height=1746 alt=Calligraphy describing U+0294 LATIN LETTER GLOTTAL STOP&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;p&gt;Today’s Unicode calligraphy highlights the &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Phonetic_Alphabet&quot;&gt;International Phonetic Alphabet&lt;/a&gt; symbol for the &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glottal_stop&quot;&gt;glottal stop&lt;/a&gt;, the sound between the syllables of “uh-oh”. (It can also be heard if you say the phrase “glottal stop” in a Cockney accent!)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Squamish_language&quot;&gt;Squamish&lt;/a&gt; orthography, the glottal stop is represented by the digit 7 instead of ʔ, as in &lt;em&gt;Sḵwx̱wú7mesh.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title>Photo of the day</title><link>https://rosschurchley.com/2025/boats-void-14/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://rosschurchley.com/2025/boats-void-14/</guid><pubDate>Mon, 03 Mar 2025 08:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/src.2ZS0h13J_Z1Q0Rmt.webp&quot; width=2048 height=1536 alt=A yellow sign reading &quot;Void #14&quot; labels the top edge of a stomach-high metal wall. Through the void can be seen concrete pillars and metal structures making up the dock infrastructure of a ferry terminal.&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;dl&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Taken&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;2004-08-17&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Location&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;Canada / BC / Victoria / Swartz Bay Ferry Terminal&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title>Photo of the day</title><link>https://rosschurchley.com/2025/boats-tugboat-hodder/</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://rosschurchley.com/2025/boats-tugboat-hodder/</guid><pubDate>Sun, 02 Mar 2025 08:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/_astro/src.DVkmeOB2_Z1iVuvm.webp&quot; width=6000 height=4000 alt=A blue and white tugboat sails leftwards up the Fraser River. Several log bundles are floating on the river on either side of the boat. The opposite bank of the river is lined by a thin forest of tall deciduous trees.&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;dl&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Taken&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;2022-04-10&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;dt&gt;Location&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;Canada / BC / Vancouver / River District&lt;/dd&gt;&lt;/dl&gt;</content:encoded></item></channel></rss>